cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with deep metric learning for image similarity. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel loss function for learning embeddings. Additionally, it could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves learning representations for semantic similarity. Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as it deals with similarity among data points, which could include various types of multimedia data. Finally, information retrieval (cs.IR) could also be a relevant sub-category as the learned embeddings could be used for similarity search and retrieval.
